    "markdown": "\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n# Ggplotly\n\n<center>![](images/ggplot2_ggplotly.png){style=\"width:200px\"}</center>\n\nPlotly is a graphing library that allows you to create interactive charts and maps. These are in the form of html files.\n\nThis works with python, R, `ggplot2`, and other languages. You can create plots with plotly's own library in R. However, we'll demonstrate how to plotlyfy plots with `ggplot2` using `ggplotly()`.\n\nThe package `plotly` is separate to `tidyverse` and therefore needs installing.\n\n[Install instruction](https://plotly.com/r/getting-started/)\n\nOnce installed you can load the library.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n[Plotly ggplotly reference page](https://plotly.com/ggplot2/)\n\n## Dataset\n\nFor demonstration we'll load the `mushroom_tbl` data from the [mgrtibbles package](/datasets/mgrtibbles.qmd) (hyperlink includes install instructions). We will extract a random sample of 150 rows with `slice_sample()`.\n\n[mushroom_tbl details](https://github.com/m-gemmell/mgrtibbles/wiki/mushroom_tbl)\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\n#Load package\nlibrary(\"mgrtibbles\")\n#Set seed for random sampling\nset.seed(\"483\")\n#mushroom_tbl tibble for demonstration\nmushroom_tbl <- mgrtibbles::mushroom_tbl |>\n    #Random sample of 150 rows\n    dplyr::slice_sample(n = 150, replace=FALSE)\n#Reset random seed to normal operation\nset.seed(NULL)\n```\n:::\n\n\n\n<div class='webex-solution'><button>View mushroom_tbl contents</button>\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"reactable html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-842e3cbe3dd05932925f\" style=\"width:auto;height:auto;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-842e3cbe3dd05932925f\">{\"x\":{\"tag\":{\"name\":\"Reactable\",\"attribs\":{\"data\":{\"class\":[\"edible\",\"poisonous\",\"edible\",\"poisonous\",\"poisonous\",\"poisonous\",\"edible\",\"edible\",\"poisonous\",\"poisonous\",\"poisonous\",\"poisonous\",\"