a ggplot pbject\n\nCreate a scatter plot of `stem_height` (y) against `stem_width` (x).\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nscatterplot <- mushroom_tbl |>\n    ggplot2::ggplot(aes(x = stem_width, y = stem_height)) +\n    ggplot2::geom_point()\n```\n:::\n\n\nNext we can pipe the ggplot object to the function `plotly::ggplotly()`.\n\nThe html based plot is interactive allowing you to:\n\n-   Zoom in horizontally, vertically, or with both axes.\n-   Rest the zoom with the home (<svg viewBox=\"0 0 576 512\" style=\"height:1em;position:relative;display:inline-block;top:.1em;fill:#648fff;\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">  <path d=\"M280.37 148.26L96 300.11V464a16 16 0 0 0 16 16l112.06-.29a16 16 0 0 0 15.92-16V368a16 16 0 0 1 16-16h64a16 16 0 0 1 16 16v95.64a16 16 0 0 0 16 16.05L464 480a16 16 0 0 0 16-16V300L295.67 148.26a12.19 12.19 0 0 0-15.3 0zM571.6 251.47L488 182.56V44.05a12 12 0 0 0-12-12h-56a12 12 0 0 0-12 12v72.61L318.47 43a48 48 0 0 0-61 0L4.34 251.47a12 12 0 0 0-1.6 16.9l25.5 31A12 12 0 0 0 45.15 301l235.22-193.74a12.19 12.19 0 0 1 15.3 0L530.9 301a12 12 0 0 0 16.9-1.6l25.5-31a12 12 0 0 0-1.7-16.93z\"></path></svg>) symbol on the top right.\n\nTry interacting with the below plot.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nscatterplot |> plotly::ggplotly()\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"plotly html-widget html-fill-item\" id=\"htmlwidget-507859dc8b44aeec1600\" style=\"width:100%;height:382px;\"></div>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"htmlwidget-507859dc8b44aeec1600\">{\"x\":{\"data\":[{\"x\":[19.219999999999999,11.460000000000001,13.92,1.0800000000000001,2.4700000000000002,14.33,13.24,9.7799999999999994,12.77,8.0399999999999991,12.34,16.280000000000001,17.309999999999999,9.4100000000000001,23.879999999999999,16.780000000000001,5.4100000000000001,31.940000000000001,3.25,13.44,10.56,2.8999999999999999,14.9,3.3100000000000001,2.7000000000000002,18.149999999999999,3.52,13.710000000000001,17.940000000000001,12.08,5.7